**Using Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD) – Secure‑by‑Design Guidance**  
*(Offensive/defensive perspective, with concrete code, configuration tables, and remediation notes)*  

---  

## 1. Overview of the Entra ID Flow  
| Phase | What Happens | Security Goal | Typical OWASP / CWE Mapping |
|-------|--------------|---------------|-----------------------------|
| **Discovery** | Application registers in Entra → obtains **client‑id**, **tenant‑id**, **redirect‑uri**. | Establish a trusted trust‑relationship. | *A07 – Identification & Authentication Failures* (CWE‑287). |
| **Authorization Request** | Browser redirects (or popup) to `https://login.microsoftonline.com/{tenant}/oauth2/v2.0/authorize` with **PKCE** (`code_challenge`). | Prevent code‑interception & CSRF. | *A02 – Cryptographic Failures* (CWE‑326). |
| **User Authentication** | Entra presents login UI (MFA, conditional access). | Verify user identity. | *A07* (CWE‑287). |
| **Token Issuance** | Entra returns **authorization code** → backend (or SPA) exchanges for **ID token** + **access token** (JWT). | Tokens are signed, time‑bounded, audience‑restricted. | *A06 – Vulnerable and Outdated Components* (CWE‑295). |
| **Token Validation** | Application validates **signature**, **iss**, **aud**, **exp**, **nonce**, **c_hash**. | Ensure token integrity & freshness. | *A06* (CWE‑295). |
| **Session Establishment** | Secure, **httpOnly** cookie (or token‑binding) stores session identifier. | Prevent XSS token theft. | *A03 – Injection (XSS)* (CWE‑79). |
| **Logout / Revocation** | Call `https://login.microsoftonline.com/{tenant}/oauth2/v2.0/logout` and clear cookies. | End SSO session. | *A07* (CWE‑613). |

---  

## 2. Minimal Secure Implementation (SPA + MSAL.js)

Below is a **defensive‑first** starter that can be dropped into `entra.html`.  
All **security‑critical** settings are highlighted and annotated.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Secure Entra‑ID Demo</title>

  <!-- 1️⃣ Content‑Security‑Policy (strict) -->
  <meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy"
        content="
          default-src 'self';
          script-src 'self' https://alcdn.msauth.net;
          style-src  'self' 'unsafe-inline';
          connect-src https://login.microsoftonline.com https://graph.microsoft.com;
          img-src    data: 'self';
          frame-ancestors 'none';
        ">

  <!-- 2️⃣ Sub‑resource Integrity for MSAL CDN -->
  <script src="https://alcdn.msauth.net/browser/2.38.0/js/msal-browser.min.js"
          integrity="sha384-<BASE64‑HASH>"
          crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>

<body>
  <h1>Secure Entra‑ID SPA</h1>
  <button id="loginBtn">Login with Microsoft</button>
  <button id="logoutBtn" style="display:none;">Logout</button>

  <script>
    // ==== 3️⃣ Configuration – never hard‑code secrets ====
    const msalConfig = {
      auth: {
        clientId:   "<YOUR_CLIENT_ID>",          // from Azure portal (public)
        authority:  "https://login.microsoftonline.com/<YOUR_TENANT_ID>",
        redirectUri: window.location.origin + "/",
        // Store auth state in httpOnly cookie (requires server support)
        // MSAL will fallback to sessionStorage if not available.
        // This flag forces cookie usage for the *state* only.
        // Tokens themselves will be stored in httpOnly cookies later.
        storeAuthStateInCookie: true
      },
      cache: {
        // **Never** use localStorage for tokens – it persists across tabs.
        cacheLocation: "sessionStorage",   // short‑lived, cleared on tab close
        storeAuthStateInCookie: true       // mitigates Safari ITP issues
      },
      system: {
        // Enable logger for dev only – never ship with logLevel = Verbose
        loggerOptions: {
          loggerCallback: (level, message, containsPii) => {
            if (containsPii) return; // never log PII
            console.log(`[MSAL ${level}] ${message}`);
          },
          piiLoggingEnabled: false,
          logLevel: msal.LogLevel.Error
        }
      }
    };

    // ==== 4️⃣ Create MSAL instance ====
    const msalInstance = new msal.PublicClientApplication(msalConfig);

    // ==== 5️⃣ Helper: Secure token storage in httpOnly cookie (server‑side) ====
    async function storeTokensSecurely(idToken, accessToken) {
      // POST to your back‑end (e.g., /api/session) that sets an httpOnly cookie.
      // The back‑end must verify the JWT signature before issuing the cookie.
      await fetch('/api/session', {
        method: 'POST',
        credentials: 'include', // send/receive cookies
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ idToken, accessToken })
      });
    }

    // ==== 6️⃣ Login flow (popup) ====
    document.getElementById('loginBtn').addEventListener('click', async () => {
      try {
        const loginResponse = await msalInstance.loginPopup({
          scopes: ["openid", "profile", "email", "User.Read"]
        });

        // Validate token claims client‑side (defense‑in‑depth)
        const idToken = loginResponse.idToken;
        const decoded = JSON.parse(atob(idToken.split('.')[1])); // no secret needed
        if (!decoded.roles?.includes('Admin')) {
          console.warn('User lacks required role – UI will be limited.');
        }

        // Send tokens to back‑end for httpOnly cookie creation
        await storeTokensSecurely(loginResponse.idToken, loginResponse.accessToken);

        // UI adjustments (client‑side *only* for convenience – never for security)
        document.getElementById('loginBtn').style.display = 'none';
        document.getElementById('logoutBtn').style.display = 'block';
      } catch (err) {
        console.error('Login failed:', err);
      }
    });

    // ==== 7️⃣ Logout flow (full IdP sign‑out) ====
    document.getElementById('logoutBtn').addEventListener('click', async () => {
      // 1️⃣ Clear server‑side session cookie
      await fetch('/api/session', { method: 'DELETE', credentials: 'include' });

      // 2️⃣ Redirect to Azure AD logout endpoint (ends SSO)
      const logoutUrl = `https://login.microsoftonline.com/${msalConfig.auth.authority.split('/').pop()}/oauth2/v2.0/logout?post_logout_redirect_uri=${encodeURIComponent(window.location.origin)}`;
      msalInstance.logoutRedirect({ postLogoutRedirectUri: window.location.origin });
      // Fallback for browsers that block redirects:
      window.location.href = logoutUrl;
    });

    // ==== 8️⃣ Silent token renewal (recommended) ====
    // Run on page load to keep session alive without UI pop‑ups.
    msalInstance.initialize().then(() => {
      msalInstance.acquireTokenSilent({
        scopes: ["User.Read"]
      }).catch(err => {
        // Silent failure → user must re‑authenticate
        console.info('Silent token acquisition failed, user interaction required.');
      });
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Key Defensive Choices in the Snippet  

| Defensive Feature | Why It Matters (OWASP / CWE) |
|-------------------|------------------------------|
| **CSP + SRI** | Blocks injection of malicious scripts that could read `sessionStorage` (A03 – XSS, CWE‑79). |
| **`storeAuthStateInCookie:true`** | Moves the OAuth *state* parameter out of `sessionStorage`, mitigating Safari ITP and XSS leakage (A03, CWE‑79). |
| **Short‑lived `sessionStorage`** | Limits token exposure to the current tab; cleared on close (reduces attack window). |
| **Server‑side token validation & httpOnly cookie** | Guarantees signature verification (A06 – Cryptographic Failures, CWE‑295) and removes tokens from JavaScript scope (A03, CWE‑79). |
| **Explicit logout via IdP endpoint** | Terminates the SSO session, preventing session‑fixation (A07, CWE‑613). |
| **Scope‑minimal request (`openid profile email User.Read`)** | Principle of least privilege – reduces token surface (A06, CWE‑522). |
| **No hard‑coded secrets** | Client‑id is public; never embed client‑secret or private keys in the front‑end (A02 – Broken Authentication). |
| **Logging without PII** | Prevents accidental credential leakage (A02, CWE‑200). |

